The paper deals with coding theory and matrix algebra, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on rank metric codes and generator matrices suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the construction of structured matrices, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of efficient criteria for verifying codes could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
